<div id="comment_status_64642064" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64642064" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64642064" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_64642064" name="comment_link_64642064" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23395126&amp;cid=64642064" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64642064)" >Re:Part of the story</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64642064" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64642064); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Eunomion">Eunomion</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Eunomion">( 8640039 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64642064">		
		on Sunday July 21, 2024 @06:10AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23395126&amp;cid=64642064">#64642064</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64642064">Nuclear does have absurd externalities.  One, the entire supply and waste chain has to be security-hardened to some degree, and nothing else has that problem.  Two, its costs continue decades to centuries after its benefits have been expended.  While you can hand-wavily claim that the rare metals in solar panels technically have a continuing environmental cost, it's obviously not the same ballpark.
<br>
<br>
The reason I make a point of this is that nuclear is a greenwashing locus, for the political segment that sees the writing on the wall but doesn't want to give up the kind of centralized control that fossil fuels allow.  It's not the most important thing to criticize, but it's worthwhile to call out lobbyist sleight-of-hand.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64642064">
