	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64642448"><p>Batteries in the wider sense include pumped hydro, and in that sense there can be used to stabilize the grid with a mix of hydro/solar/wind.  Nuclear could also be used as a base load, but has LOTS of problems.  It's expensive, it takes a long time to build, it's really hard to decommission, and the "waste" really needs to be recycled, but that threatens nuclear proliferation,  Molten salt reactors could probably, in principle, solve those problems, but that's a technology that isn't quite ready yet.</p><p>OTOH, I<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64642448">

